6. MODULE COMPONENTS (Customization) 

Limit: 1 Active Module and 2 Passive Modules equipped at once (Standard Form). 

Active Modules (10-Second Duration) 

Module 

Effect 

Strategic Use 

Death Mark 

Target takes 50% increased damage from all sources. 

Perfect for focusing down bosses or high-threat targets. 

Phase Shift 

Dimensional ghosting. Visible but immune to all damage. 

Essential for surviving massive area-of-effect attacks. 

Advanced Repair 

Restores 20% of maximum HP over the duration. 

Keeps FALANX in the fight during intense frontline pressure. 

Shield Breaker 

Disables enemy shields, leaving them fully vulnerable. 

Used to crack open high-defense targets or stationary turrets. 

Quantum Radar 

Grants full visibility, including invisible/cloaked units. 

Counters ambush units and stealth-based "glitch" fighters. 

Lockdown 

Attacks apply "Lockdown" status; targets cannot move when full. 

To pin down fast enemies and keep them in the Miasma Cloud. 

Passive Modules (Standard Form) 

Module 

Effect 

Why Pick This? 

Last Stand 

Immunity to ALL damage for 5s when HP drops to 5%. 

Provides a final window to retreat or secure a desperate kill. 

Overdrive Unit 

Deal +10% Damage when health is below 30%. 

High-risk, high-reward; turns damage taken into raw power. 

Accelerator 

Permanent 10% movement speed boost. 

Increases general mobility for better positioning and dodging. 

Heavy Armor Kit 

Increases FALANX's Max HP by 10%. 

Solid defensive baseline for increased survivability. 

Anticontrol 

Removes all debuffs when 3+ are active; grants temp immunity. 

Essential for breaking out of "CC chains" and negative statuses. 

Fortifier 

All Shield layers (Ancile/Aegis) gain +10% HP. 

Maximizes the effectiveness of the Pilot's layered defense systems. 

7. COMBAT STRATEGY 

Attrition: FALANX wins by making the battlefield uninhabitable. 

Titan Logic: Enter Titan form when the enemy is bunched up. Use Fortress Mode to protect your team while Solar Flare slows enemies and Gas Spread blinds them. 

Antimatter Choice: If choosing the Antimatter Reactor in Titan Form, stay at range to let the Miasma Spreader's matured chemical payload deal devastating damage. 

 
